@startuml fig-websocket-upgrade-proxy
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title WebSocket Handshake via Reverse Proxy

participant "Browser" as B #FFE0B2
participant "Nginx\nReverse Proxy" as N #E3F2FD
participant "WebSocket Server\n:9000" as WS #C8E6C9

== HTTP Upgrade Handshake ==

B -> N : GET /ws\nUpgrade: websocket\nConnection: Upgrade\nSec-WebSocket-Key: ...
N -> WS : GET /ws\nUpgrade: websocket\nConnection: Upgrade\nSec-WebSocket-Key: ...

WS -[#43A047]-> N : 101 Switching Protocols\nSec-WebSocket-Accept: ...
N -[#43A047]-> B : 101 Switching Protocols\nSec-WebSocket-Accept: ...

== WebSocket Frames (bidirectional) ==

B -[#1565C0]> WS : {"type":"join","room":"networks"}
WS -[#43A047]-> B : {"type":"joined","room":"networks"}

B -[#1565C0]> WS : {"type":"msg","text":"Hello"}
WS -[#43A047]-> B : {"type":"deliver","id":1,...}
WS -[#43A047]-> B : {"type":"ack","id":1}

legend right
  The connection begins as an HTTP request.
  After 101 Switching Protocols it becomes
  a persistent, full-duplex frame protocol.
  Nginx must support proxy_set_header Upgrade.
endlegend
@enduml
